    "comment": "Rationale: Fig3B: Homogenates of brainstem and spinal cord were fractionated and stained with antibodies directed against syntenin-1, PSD-95, and synaptophysin. Syntenin1 was found in the crude synaptosome fraction (P2) and present in the synaptic membrane (LP1) and synaptic vesicle (LP2) fractions.\n\nFig6A-B: GST-syntenin1 pull-down reveals differently sized syntaxin 1A complexes (arrows) in rat brain extract. Boiling of the samples and Western analysis with different antibodies shows that the three components of the SNARE complex, syntaxin 1A, SNAP25, and synaptobrevin-2, all co-precipitate with GST-syntenin-1 from the brain extract indicating a presynaptic localization.\n\nFigure 3: The antibody specificity was tested by Western blot from brain lysates that recognised the calculate MW (~36 kDa) of syntenin1.. Experimental description: Subcellular fractions of adult rat brainstem and spinal cord were prepared as described by Li et al. (1996). Species of the rat wasn't mentioned in the paper. Polyclonal antibodies against rat syntenin-1 (1:500) is described in Koroll et al., 2001.",
